TITLE: Reactive Interface with Rx.Subject in Inquirer.js
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use the reactive interface in Inquirer.js with Rx.Subject to dynamically add questions to be asked. It creates a new Rx.Subject, pushes new question objects to it, and then calls complete() when done.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sboudrias/inquirer.js/blob/main/packages/inquirer/README.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const prompts = new Rx.Subject();
inquirer.prompt(prompts);

// At some point in the future, push new questions
prompts.next({
  /* question... */
});
prompts.next({
  /* question... */
});

// When you're done
prompts.complete();
```

