TITLE: Asking a question conditionally - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates how to ask a question based on the answer to a previous question. It first asks the user if they allow email communication. If the user confirms, it then prompts for their email address. This conditional logic allows for a more dynamic and personalized user experience.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sboudrias/inquirer.js/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { input, confirm } from '@inquirer/prompts';

const allowEmail = await confirm({ message: 'Do you allow us to send you email?' });

let email;
if (allowEmail) {
  email = await input({ message: 'What is your email address' });
}
```

