TITLE: Using the @inquirer/checkbox Prompt
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to import and use the @inquirer/checkbox prompt to create an interactive checkbox selection in the command line. It showcases defining choices, including separators, and handling disabled options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sboudrias/inquirer.js/blob/main/packages/checkbox/README.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import { checkbox, Separator } from '@inquirer/prompts';
// Or
// import checkbox, { Separator } from '@inquirer/checkbox';

const answer = await checkbox({
  message: 'Select a package manager',
  choices: [
    { name: 'npm', value: 'npm' },
    { name: 'yarn', value: 'yarn' },
    new Separator(),
    { name: 'pnpm', value: 'pnpm', disabled: true },
    {
      name: 'pnpm',
      value: 'pnpm',
      disabled: '(pnpm is not available)',
    },
  ],
});
```

