TITLE: Rendering Function with done Callback (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example illustrates the basic structure of a rendering function within `createPrompt`.  It shows how to return a string to be displayed as the prompt and how to use the `done` callback to complete the prompt and return the answer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sboudrias/inquirer.js/blob/main/packages/core/README.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const input = createPrompt((config, done) => {
  const [value, setValue] = useState();

  useKeypress((key, readline) => {
    if (key.name === 'enter') {
      done(answer);
    } else {
      setValue(readline.line);
    }
  });

  return `? ${config.message} ${value}`;
});
```

